 Description:
 The Joint Effects Targeting System (JETS) supports the Army's fires sensor strategy and is aligned with the Army's priorities in support of the National Defense Strategy. The JETS satisfies the requirement for
 the dismounted precision targeting sensor for the individual observer. The system provides the individual dismounted observer with an integrated, lightweight, modular capability to detect, identify, and accurately
 locate targets in three dimensions. The JETS also provides the capability to laser mark and designate targets for weapons platforms and transmits accurate target location coordinates to a forward entry system
 for engagement with precision munitions. The JETS is an Army program with joint interest with the Air Force and Marine Corps. The PM is exploring and assessing emerging technologies with the Fires Center
 of Excellence (FCoE) for a Handheld Fires system materiel solution, which will produce similar capabilities as the JETS II System but at a reduced cost. Procurement of Handheld Fires (HHF) hardware will
 commence in FY29.

 The Army Acquisition Objective (AAO) for JETS is 3,355.
