 Description:
 The Mortar Fire Control System (MFCS) accurately determines weapon position and orientation, navigates, calculates ballistics, and communicates digitally on the Fires Support Network. The MFCS main Line
 Replaceable Units (LRUs) are: the Fire Control Computer (FCC), Enhanced Power Distribution Assembly (EPDA), Inertial Navigation Unit (INU), Portable Universal Battery Supply (PUBS), Gunner's Display
 (GD), and cable sets. Mortar Fire Control System Modifications efforts support the current MFCS mounted and dismounted variants as well as Lightweight Handheld Mortar Ballistic Computer (LHMBC) and
 future modernized mortar fire control systems, and enable the replacement of aging/obsolete major system components. Modification efforts include Military-Code (M-Code) integration, lightweight weapon
 pointing device upgrades, the transition to Modular Open Systems Architecture, the transition to common mortar application software and Graphical User Interface (GUI), and the implementation of software
 upgrades in accordance with Army Directive 2024-2 (Enabling Modern Software Development & Acquisition).
