 Justification:
 FY 2027 Base procurement dollars in the amount of $61.127 million procures the following AMDPCS shelters: one (1) AMDPCS-B shelter system, three (3) Air Battle Management Operations Centers (ABMOCs)
 shelters, and eight (8) Sensor C2 Node shelter for Army National Guard M-SHORAD Battalions. Base dollars also procure net ready hardware for seven (7) AMDPCS-A & B shelter systems, forty (40) ADAM
 shelters in conjunction with Engineering Change Proposals (ECPs) and Modification Work Orders (MWOs), and 343 AMDPCS workstations and associated software and support (AMDWS, FAAD and CDLI-M)
 for AMDPCS shelter systems. Finally, these procurement dollars include program management, shipping/fielding costs, and New Equipment Training (NET).

 In accordance with Section 1815 of the FY 2008 National Defense Authorization Act (P.L. 110-181), this item is necessary for use by the active and reserve components of the Armed Forces for homeland
 defense missions, domestic emergency responses, and providing the military support to civil authorities.

 Increase from FY 2026 to FY 2027 reflects an increase in AMDPCS shelter procurement quantities. AMDPCS Workstations quantities vary with the multiple shelter LINs/configurations (AMDPCS-A, AMDPCS-B,
 ADAM Cell, ABMOC, Battery CP, and Sensor C2 Node), each has a different unit cost, which results in fluctuation of unit cost by year, based on the quantities procured in support of Army fielding requirements.

 Prior Year quantity of 35 is incorrect, the correct prior quantity is 441.




