 Description:
 This funding supports the Army's Next Generation Command Control (NGC2) initiative to modernize the Command and Control (C2) systems Infrastructure Layer to secure battlefield superiority. NGC2 is one
 of the Army's highest modernization priorities and will enhance the Army's ability to conduct multi-domain operations by integrating advanced technologies, improving interoperability, and increasing the speed
 and accuracy of decision-making processes. The NGC2 ecosystem is a full stack of capabilities with integrated warfighting systems in the Application Layer, supported by an integrated Data Layer that operates
 seamlessly over both cloud and edge computing within the Infrastructure Layer, and integrates with/autonomously uses a variety of network solutions in the Transport Layer.

 Beginning in FY 2027, 9705BA9301 / Network Management Initialization and Services funding has been realigned to B11400 as part of a new funding structure for the Next Generation Command and Control
 (NGC2) investment to modernize Command and Control (C2) systems for the Infrastructure Layer.

 The Network Management Initialization and Services (NMIS) program supports the Army's objective of an integrated Network Operations capability. There are three components to the program:

 Joint Network Management System (JNMS), B99318, this specific funding supports Joint and NGC2 initiatives to modernize Command and Control (C2) systems. The JNMS project provides training and logistics
 activities for Joint Enterprise Network Manager (JENM) / Joint Network Management Software planning applications and radio planner prototyping efforts, which provide Lower Tactical Tier Network planning,
 configuration, monitoring and troubleshooting and other Army Capability Manager (ACM) approved applications supporting the Unified Network (UN) and its emerging requirements. JNMS funding provides
 critical support to all Army warfighting functions Division/Brigade Combat Teams (BCTs), U.S. Army support elements, ITN experimental units, and Security Forces Assistance Brigades (SFABs).

 Unified Network Operations (UNO), B99418:
 This project supports the Army's NGC2 Infrastructure Layer by providing the infrastructure, services and support critical to establishing a unified, network-centric battlefield that empowers commanders with
 unprecedented situational awareness and control, enabling rapid planning, resource allocation, and execution through robust applications, infrastructure, and resilient communication networks. The Army's NGC2
 initiative fundamentally transforms Army operations by moving beyond isolated systems to integrate all warfighting functions - Command and Control (C2), Information Advantage, Movement and Maneuver,
 Intelligence, Fires, Protection, Sustainment, and Network Operations (NetOps) - into a cohesive ecosystem. Built upon a Zero Trust Architecture, NGC2 will continuously verify all users and devices before
 granting access to resources, minimizing the impact of potential breaches, and ensuring data integrity across the NGC2 environment.

 Data Products, BA9315:



