 Description:
 The Ammunition Peculiar Equipment (APE) program provides a vast array of equipment and support for ammunition operations including surveillance, demilitarization, maintenance, refurbishment, modification,
 packaging, and preservation per Army Regulation 700-20. This program is developed, acquired, and supervised through the Single Manager for Conventional Ammunition per DoDI 5160.68. APE provides
 equipment items specifically designed, fabricated, procured, tested, and adopted for use in worldwide United States military ammunition depot operations on conventional ammunition. APE maintains a central
 source of standard, modern, safe, efficient, reliable, and environmentally acceptable equipment for ammunition operations.
 The APE mission is critical to all Organic Demilitarization Operations, and is utilized to demilitarize ammunition items into components, sorts and removes hazardous materials to reduce human interaction
 and improves personnel safety. Demilitarization APE items perform disassembly, incineration, deformation, shredding and other processes. APE supporting Maintenance is designed to perform cleaning and
 renovation functions on ammunition subjected to deterioration effects (rust, corrosion, weathering, etc.) during its storage life. APE supporting Surveillance are key to stockpile sampling and functional testing of
 the items to assure readiness for combat or training. The APE program also supports warehouse operations at the APE National Inventory Control Point (NICP), executing the movement (receiving and shipment)
 of APE equipment worldwide.




