 Description:
 Empowering the warfighter and global partners, Cyber Security & Analytics (CS&A) is the backbone of secure DoW mission operations. CS&A delivers strategic, innovative, and optimized cyber infrastructure that
 ensures resilient communication and protects vital information assets. Through a comprehensive joint information assurance model, CS&A proactively mitigates risks, enables seamless and secure information
 sharing across all classification levels, and stands as the frontline defense against dynamic cybersecurity threats.

 Capabilities provided include:

 • Cyber Analytics: CS&A strategically develops and deploys Department-level cyber analytics and tools to revolutionize DoW cyber information sharing, ensuring agile and adaptive defense of the DoW
 Information Networks (DoWIN). A cornerstone of this capability is an advanced sensor network. This distributed system actively monitors diverse network locations, channeling vital data to a central repository for
 real-time aggregation and in-depth analysis, transforming raw data into actionable intelligence for rapid threat mitigation.

 • Enterprise Perimeter Defenses: Functioning as the essential cybersecurity barrier between the public internet and the DoW Non-Classified Internet Protocol Router Network (NIPRNet), the DoW's perimeter
 defense systems are responsible for safeguarding the entire DoW enterprise. These defenses are particularly crucial for protecting against web and email-based attacks. Furthermore, these Perimeter Defenses
 utilize specialized capabilities to enable the secure sharing of classified defense and intelligence information with mission partners outside of the DoW. In accordance with the Fiscal Year 2024 National Defense
 Authorization Act (NDAA), which mandates the modernization of Perimeter Defense, DISA is directing resources to enhance threat intelligence, improve the automated mitigation of threats at the boundary,
 increase the volume of decrypted traffic at the perimeter, and strengthen security for DoW users behind Cloud Based Internet Isolation (CBII) through the implementation of Artificial Intelligence (AI) based
 features.

 • Perimeter Modernization Secret Internet Protocol Router Releasable (SIPR REL): The SIPR REL gateway enables secure, direct access for Five Eyes partners to the Secret Internet Protocol Router Network
 (SIPRNet). This critical capability facilitates the rapid and secure exchange of classified defense and intelligence information among Five Eyes nations. By empowering allies and partners to operate as combat
 multipliers, SIPR REL significantly enhances collective capabilities and readiness, directly supporting the Secretary of War's priority to reestablish deterrence and defend the homeland.




