 Justification:
 Situational Awareness is a primary objective of the Chemical Biological Defense Program. Operational forces must safely operate, survive, and sustain operations in a chemical and biological agent threat
 environment. Contamination Avoidance maintains operational efficiency and minimizes the need to decontaminate vehicles, equipment, and areas. Advanced chemical and biological defensive equipment
 strengthens the US's capability to detect and identify threat agents in the battle space and the homeland.
 Warning, reporting, and reconnaissance efforts enable a tiered strategy detecting and warning complementary detection/identification systems to provide theater protection against large area and point attacks.
 Supports Special Purpose Unit operations and the National Guard Bureau Weapons of Mass Destruction Civil Support Teams (WMD-CSTs).




