 Justification:
 White House Situation Support Staff (WHSSS)

 WHSSS provides critical information technology, classified communications, computer, and intelligence support for the White House Situation Room (WHSR), the National Security Staff, and other White House
 offices. WHSSS delivers the ability to meet and maintain a rate of 99.99 percent reliable telecommunications and information services through state-of-the-art equipment and technology, at the best possible price
 to the public.

 FY 2025: $5.736 million - Upgrades the White House secure IT infrastructure, supporting classified voice, data, and video networks for the President, Vice President, and senior White House and National
 Security Council staff. These systems also support Continuity of Operations (COOP) and Continuity of Government (COG) locations, trip sites, and residences. To address increasingly sophisticated cyber
 threats, WHSR implements new capabilities, including 24x7 network monitoring, increased bandwidth, and architectural security upgrades. WHSR enhances organizational security and improves reliability for
 multi-level voice networks.

 FY 2026: $6.125 million - Enables the continued upgrade of the White House secure critical IT systems infrastructure that supports the classified voice, data, applications, and video networks for the U.S.
 President, Vice President, and senior White House and National Security Council senior staff. These systems are also used at White House COOP and COG locations, trip sites, and residences for the White
 House's most senior principals. WHSSS ensures uninterrupted performance of secure IT applications by establishing a Network Operations Center (NOC) within a WHSSS secure facility in the New Executive
 Office Building.

 Explanation of Change from FY 2025 to FY 2026: +$0.389 million - The increase supports equipment and infrastructure modernization of the WHSSS secure facility in the New Executive Office Building to ensure
 a fully operational NOC. The additional funding covers all project costs for the technical refresh of this space.

 FY 2027: $0.000 million – No funding requested for WHSSS procurement.

 Explanation of Change from FY 2026 to FY 2027: -$6.125 million - Decrease due to a strategic transfer from Procurement to Operations & Maintenance (O&M). Following the successful completion of a major
 renovation, the WHSR requires dedicated funding to sustain the information technology, audio-visual, and communications infrastructure that supports its modernized operations. Continued sustainment will lead
 to uninterrupted, secure, and high-speed communication, enabling the WHSR to provide 24/7 global situational awareness, crisis management facilitation, secure conference facilities, emergency actions support,
 and executive communications directly for the President of the United States in his roles as Commander-in-Chief of the Armed Forces, Head of State, and Chief Executive.

 WHSSS Performance Metrics

 1. Percentage of Classified Process Review: Conducts quarterly Independent Process Reviews to maximize performance. Status is electronically monitored for outages to ensure 99.99% reliable classified
 telecommunications and information services.

