 Description:
 The Joint Service Provider (JSP) (J6 Pentagon) serves as the sole Information Technology (IT) service provider for over 30 facilities within the Pentagon Reservation and the National Capital Region (NCR). JSP
 is responsible for operating, maintaining, and defending a highly available IT infrastructure, delivering essential mission support services to more than 55,000 customers.

 JSP prioritizes strategic investments in IT infrastructure modernization to proactively reduce operational and cyber risks. These refreshes accelerate the adoption of DoW Enterprise services, guaranteeing DoW
 components access to cutting-edge IT capabilities. By concurrently minimizing risk and integrating advanced solutions, JSP effectively mitigates evolving cybersecurity threats. Procurement funding directly
 supports this lifecycle modernization, covering IT infrastructure, hardware, and software across departmental Local Area Networks (LANs), computer servers, network storage, and supporting subsystems for over
 110,000 end-user devices.

 A critical component of DISA's role as a service provider includes senior leadership communications managed by the Secretary of War Communications Office (SECWARCOMS). Adhering to DoW guidelines,
 SECWARCOMS ensures the Secretary of War maintains resilient communication and situational awareness capabilities at the Pentagon. This responsibility includes providing access to alternative operating
 facilities and seamless mobile communications during transit, empowering the Secretary and their Immediate Office to coordinate national defense effectively in any scenario.




