 Description:
 The DTRA Cyber Activities budget line-item supports the following mission requirements:

 - Lifecycle replacement of a deployable toolkit designed to provide a lightweight flyaway/portable kit configured with high-end systems pre-loaded with next generation cyber security technologies and software;

 - Lifecycle replacement of end-of-life equipment, evolution of current technologies in support of Agency Zero Trust architecture requirements, and procurement for additional equipment to comply with Department
 of War (DoW) Cyber operation orders; and

 - Licensing and support of cybersecurity tool suites, network monitoring and logging capability; allowing for comprehensive network and system visibility, including real-time threat detection and historical data
 analysis.

 Justification:
 The FY 2025 budget of $3.429 million resourced the following efforts:

 - Procurement of a deployable toolkit used to enhance DTRA's cyber capability and fully integrate cyber as part of its holistic mission assurance threat assessment capability to ensure that interdependent
 physical and cyber vulnerabilities are identified, and risk decisions can be made by senior leaders;

 - Upgraded system storage, hardware, and software that have become obsolete due to evolving technology; and

 - Provided lifecycle replacement, including hardware/software, licensing of cybersecurity tool suites that integrate into the enterprise Security Incident Event Manager, and network logging capability that allows
 for network and system visibility and provides enterprise network/system log review, alerting, and data retention. This enables DTRA to meet requirements in both the Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff (CJCS)
 Instruction 6510.0 (Information Assurance and Support to Computer Network Defense) and Department of Defense Instruction (DoDI) 8510.01 (Risk Management Framework for DoD Information Technology).

 The FY 2026 budget of $1.800 million funds the following efforts:



