Justification:
The FY 2026 Spend plan amount for MQ-9 Unmanned Aerial Vehicle includes $12.890 million of discretionary and $11.990 million of mandatory (reconciliation) for a total of $24.880 million.

FY 2027 PROGRAM JUSTIFICATION: Leverages other service and activity to fielded capabilities to rapidly procure SO-p mission kits, mission payloads, weaponization, modifications, production support, and
for Adaptive Airborne Enterprise to accelerate integration on MQ-9, Ground Control Stations, and training systems. Adaptive Airborne Enterprise (A2E) leverages current MQ-9 availability with small Unmanned
Aircraft Systems (sUAS) to close mission gaps in contested and denied environments by fielding integrated capability increments to provide increased mission support to the warfighter. The MQ-9 mission
support has evolved to contested and denied environments, driving the need to procure payloads for employment of A2E capabilities.

FY 2026 to FY 2027 increase of $62.951 million supports A2E planned purchase of ISR 600 Airborne Launched Effects (ALE); ALE small Uncrewed Aircraft System (sUAS); Swarm Carrier (SC) sUAS, and
Signature Managed sUAS. In addition, MQ-9 will procure additional payloads to support warfighter missions.




