 Justification:
 The FY 2027 request for SM-3 Block IIA includes $778.964 million of discretionary and $3,439.640 million of mandatory for a total of $4,218.604 million. The mandatory FY 2027 funds for SM-3 Block IIA provide
 for procurement of up to one hundred fourteen (114) SM-3 Block IIA All-Up Rounds (AURs), which is consistent with validated requirements and industrial base capacity.

 The discretionary FY 2027 funds provide for procurement of twenty-two (22) SM-3 Block IIA AURs. The increase in discretionary funds from FY 2026 to FY 2027 provides for Investment Spares, Pressure
 Vessel Rotatable Pool, production improvements to increase SM-3 Block IIA capacity from two (2) AURs per month to three (3) AURs per month and AUR quantity from 12 AURs to 22 AURs in support of Missile
 Defense System - Next.

 The FY 2026 spend plan amount for SM-3 Block IIA includes $444.835 million of discretionary and $65 million of mandatory (reconciliation) for a total of $509.835 million. The FY 2026 discretionary budget
 request includes 12 AURs, hardware, and support costs including canisters, production engineering, obsolescence, production improvements, pressure vessel rotatable pool, and production line improvements.

 The FY 2025 discretionary budget request includes 12 AURs, hardware, and support costs including canisters, production engineering, obsolescence, and system engineering.




