 Justification:
 FY 2027 This program contains a New Start.


 1. NSAv. This effort supports worldwide SOF missions and must have flexible capabilities to facilitate Theater Special Operations Command (TSOC) tactical and strategic objectives. The NSAv program provides
 flexible and rapid, responsive operational support of special operations teams. Support to TSOCs and operational mission objectives include SOF team mobility in remote locations, casualty evacuation, non-
 combatant evacuation operations, and humanitarian assistance.

 FY 2027 BASE PROGRAM JUSTIFICATION: Begins NSAv recapitalization by replacing the legacy C-146A with a more capable and commercially available aircraft that will provide more cost effective operations
 and less expensive lifecycle costs; completes draw down and divestment of C-146A aircraft as the recapitalized assets begin operating.

 FY 2026 to FY 2027 increase of $64.801 million includes $11.400 million increase for the procurement of two obsolescence and safety kits for the C-27J aircraft, $55.000 million increase to procure three NSAv
 aircraft and $1.599 million decrease in Low Cost Modifications. The current C-146A fleet will be divested of on a schedule that maintains this critical TSOC capability, as transition to the new aircraft occurs.




