 Description:
 This Line item is part of the Military Intelligence Program (MIP). The Distributed Common Ground/Surface System Special Operations Forces (DCGS-SOF) is part of a family of systems providing rapid fielding
 of Intelligence, Surveillance, and Reconnaissance Processing, Exploitation, Dissemination (PED), and analytical capabilities at the Combatant Command (COCOMs) and Component/Theater Special Operations
 Commands (TSOC) level and below through a combination of reach back, forward support, and collaboration. The mission tailored architecture interconnects the Warfighter, Analysts and Sensors to Find
 and Fix High-Value Targets and ensures continual, unimpeded sharing of intelligence data, information, and services across the Defense Intelligence Information Enterprise, including operations in denied,
 disconnected, intermittent, or low bandwidth environments.

 FY 2026 to FY 2027 funding decrease of $2.824 million is due to Budget Line Items (BLI) consolidation: Beginning in FY 2027, funding transitioned from P-1 Line Item 020401INTLINTL/Distributed Common
 Ground/Surface System into 020400INTL/Intelligence Systems.




