 Justification:
 1. Aircraft Support. This effort provides various types of equipment and minor modifications to support Special Operations Forces (SOF) fixed wing aircraft, and Simulator Block Upgrades (SBUD) required to
 support training transformation initiatives to modernize the Air Force Special Operations Command (AFSOC) fixed wing simulator and training device portfolio. Beginning in FY 2027, these activities will be
 executed out of P-1 Line Item 2012C130J/AC/MC-130J.

 FY 2027 PROGRAM JUSTIFICATION: The Simulator Block Upgrade (SBUD) program procures hardware/software to support training transformation capability deliveries to the operational unit and formal training
 units across the AFSOC enterprise to further increase the fidelity, quality, and efficiency of the AFSOC training pipeline.

 FY 2026 to FY 2027 decrease of $3.756 million is due to a strategic decision to transfer the SBUD training transformation procurement program to the P-1 Line Item 2012C130J/AC/MC-130Jstarting in FY 2027.

 2. Military Construction Collateral Equipment. This effort procures collateral equipment for SOF MILCON facilities. Funding provides collateral equipment for the following MILCON projects: P909 SOF SDVT2
 Operations Support Facility and P325 SOF Human Performance Training Center (JEB Little Creek-Fort Story, VA), P821 SOF Operations Support Facility and P823 SOF Operations Support Facility Phase 2
 (Coronado, CA), 1075442 SOF AFSOC Operations Center (Hurlburt Field, FL), 81905 SOF Consolidated Rigging Facility (Hunter Army Airfield, GA), 81906 SOF Military Free Fall Advanced Training Complex
 (Yuma, AZ), 81907 SOF Consolidated Rigging Facility (JB Lewis-McChord, WA), P1075 SOF Operations Building Addition and P824 SOF Demolition Training Compound Expansion (Dam Neck, VA), P1538 SOF
 Armory (Camp LeJeune, NC), 96010 SOF Arms Room Addition and 86027 SWCS Company Operations Facility (Fort Bragg, NC).

 FY 2027 PROGRAM JUSTIFICATION: Provides information technology equipment, video monitoring, intrusion detection systems, and other equipment above the Operation and Maintenance threshold of $350
 thousand, as well as items that are centrally managed.

 FY 2026 to FY 2027 increase of $22.013 million is due to large collateral equipment requirements for projects 81905 $5.365 million, 81906 $6.222 million and P821/P823 $10.426 million.


