Justification:
The FY 2026 spend plan amount for Combatant Craft Systems includes $7.000 million of discretionary and $36.440 million of mandatory (reconciliation) funding for a total of $43.440 million.

1. Combatant Craft Medium (CCM), Program Number 818, consists of the legacy CCM Mk1 and evolutionary replacement CCM Mk2, and is Naval Special Warfare's (NSW's) craft-of-choice for long-range, high-
payload SOF mobility operations in contested environments. The CCM Mk1 is a semi-enclosed multi-role surface combatant craft with a primary mission of inserting and extracting SOF Operators and deploying
kinetic and non-kinetic effects. CCM Mk2 is a purpose built, low observable (LO) surface maritime craft designed for independent, clandestine, or joint operations. Provide unfettered access, craft based effects
and targeting, theater network integration scalable endurance and range. Both variants are C-17/C-5 transportable and can launch/recover by a gray hull well deck or shore-based trailer. The CCM supports
SOF in the realm of integrated deterrence, enhance maritime security through patrols and surveillance missions, and its speed and agility combined with mobility enables rapid response and supports distributed
Maritime operations when required. Continued investment in this craft ensures efficient and sustainable capabilities which establish our competitive advantage, enable assured access in contested maritime
environments, and posture SOF and the Joint Force to meet challenges of persistent transboundary threats and future operating environments. Additionally, this platform provides access into contested areas to
enable effects that may have previously required support from the Submarine Force, ensuring that NSW can continue supporting the joint fires plans even with an asset constrained submarine force. The CCM
Mk1 program is utilizing the Major Capability Acquisition (MCA) pathway and CCM Mk2 program is utilizing the Middle Tier Acquisition (MTA) pathway.

FY2027 Base Program Justification: Funds procurement of CCM Mk2 long lead material, pre-production activities, and Government Furnished Equipment (GFE). Continues the procurement and integration
of communication and sensor suite upgrades to the CCM Mk1 fleet. These capabilities allow CCM to have further access into contested/denied areas and improve its capabilities in the joint fire exercises with
surface combatants.

FY2026 to FY2027 Increase of $11.896 million supports an $8.400 million increase for CCM Mk2 long lead material (8x engines and drives, aluminum plate) and pre-production activities to build second
production fixture, and a $3.496 million increase to continue the procurement of craft capability enhancements (communications).

Note: FY 2026 President's Budget included $0.00 million of discretionary and $13.318 million of mandatory funding for CCM.


