 Description:
 The P-8A Multi-mission Maritime Aircraft (MMA) system is a heavily modified and militarized derivative of Boeing's 737-800 ERX commercial aircraft. P-8A is Department of War's (DoW's) only long-range
 full-spectrum Anti-Submarine Warfare (ASW), cue-to-kill platform, with substantial armed Anti-Surface Warfare (ASuW) and networked Intelligence, Surveillance, and Reconnaissance (ISR) capabilities. The
 procurement funds the production of the aircraft, training systems, and associated support equipment in response to the DoW's requirement to field and sustain P-8A capabilities and readiness necessary for a
 wartime tempo.




