 Description:
 The E-2D Advanced Hawkeye (AHE) is an all-weather, twin engine, carrier-based, Airborne Command, Control and Surveillance aircraft designed to extend task force defense perimeters. The AHE mission
 is to provide advance warning of approaching enemy surface units and aircraft, to vector interceptors or strike aircraft to attack, and to provide area surveillance, intercept, search and rescue, communications
 relay, and strike/air traffic control. Key AHE objectives include improved battle space target detection and situational awareness, especially in the littorals; support of Theater Air Missile Defense operations; and
 improved Operational Availability.

 0195 BLI Prior Year includes E-2C Procurement (Qty 44)

 0195 BLI procurement quantity (qty) baseline for E-2D was increased by 11 from 75 to 86 per the R3B memo dated 19 July 2019. It identified the requirement for 11 additional E-2D aircraft that are necessary to
 fill fleet aircraft shortfalls due to insufficient pipeline and scheduled aircraft modifications. As of FY 2026 the program has been funded for 85 E-2D's.

 The FY27 budget funds the procurement of 12 additional E-2Ds (6 in FY27, 2 in FY28 and 4 in FY29) to replenish accelerated service life burn down of existing force structure due to Overland Airborne Early
 Warning (AEW) tasking. It also includes Advanced Procurement (AP) funding in FY27 and FY28 to support the FY28 and FY29 procurements.




